org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.datatype

Class OntStateChange.Continuous

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.datatype.OntStateChange.Continuous
  • Enclosing class:
    OntStateChange<T>

    public static class OntStateChange.Continuous
extends Object
    This subclass defines an concrete instance/type of a state change of OntStateChange. It should be used, if the state change is not manipulated as far and the state value(s) based on continuous values (e.g. numbers like hsb).

    • Constructor Detail

      • Continuous

        public Continuous(String timestamp,
                  List<org.apache.jena.rdf.model.RDFNode> stateValues)
           throws org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException
        Constructor creates an continuous state change instance, which based on not manipulated state values (literals like e.g. 17.35^^xsd:int) to store them. The information parts (input argument) will be convert to specific data types (see getter of this class).
        Parameters:
        timestamp - is the timestamp at which the state change occurred. Must be parsable to OffsetDateTime.
        stateValues - is the value (literal type) of the state change. The rdf nodes must be based on literals.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException - is thrown in case at least one input parameter is null/invalid or one state value isn't a literal (continuous value).
